verses.verse: A <S%H7892>Song<s%> of <S%H4609>degrees.<s%> <S%H413>Unto<s%> thee lift I <S%H5375>up<s%> <S%H853><s%> mine <S%H5869>eyes,<s%> O thou that <S%H3427>dwellest<s%> in the <S%H8064>heavens.<s%>

Behold, <S%H2009><s%> as the <S%H5869>eyes<s%> of <S%H5650>servants<s%> look <S%H413>unto<s%> the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of their <S%H113>masters,<s%> and as the <S%H5869>eyes<s%> of a <S%H8198>maiden<s%> <S%H413>unto<s%> the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of her <S%H1404>mistress;<s%> <S%H3651>so<s%> our <S%H5869>eyes<s%> wait <S%H413>upon<s%> the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> our <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H5704>until<s%> that he have mercy <S%H7945>upon<s%> <S%H2603><s%> us.
Have mercy <S%H2603>upon<s%> us, O <S%H3068>LORD,<s%> have mercy <S%H2603>upon<s%> us: <S%H3588>for<s%> we are <S%H7227>exceedingly<s%> <S%H7646>filled<s%> with <S%H937>contempt.<s%>

Our <S%H5315>soul<s%> is <S%H7227>exceedingly<s%> <S%H7646>filled<s%> with the <S%H3933>scorning<s%> of those that are at <S%H7600>ease,<s%> and with the <S%H937>contempt<s%> of the <S%H1349>proud.<s%>
